{
  "texts": [
    "Through these years, several companies and research groups have made some advancements in relatively integrating DTs and on-the-chip technologies.",
    "In the case of drug development, the DigiLoCS framework represents a significant advancement in predictive pharmacokinetics.",
    "DigiLoCS combines the detailed biological data from liver-on-chip systems with sophisticated mathematical models to visually represent the liver's drug processing functions.",
    "DigiLoCS models complex biological processes, such as drug metabolism, permeability, and partitioning, within the liver-on-chip system, and it has been shown to outperform traditional methods in predicting human liver clearance.",
    "One of the main challenges in integrating DTs with organ-on-chip systems is accurately modeling the complex interactions within the liver."
  ]
}